main event: Two spherical, orange-colored flying objects were observed off the coast of Mayaguez, Puerto Rico by civilians on May 11, 1952 between 1900-1930 hours.
interesting points: One of the objects was stationary, while the other object darted around.
The observers were described as people of sound judgment, including a Puerto Rican businessman and lawyer, an American ex-Air Force pilot, and a Puerto Rican college student.
An attempt was made to take a photograph, but the examination of the negative revealed nothing.
No attempt at interception was possible.
The weather conditions were clear with excellent visibility.
witnesses: civilian observers, including a businessman, lawyer, ex-Air Force pilot, and college student
